<taxonomicName box="[1263,1436,839,863]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Sitana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ponticeriana">
<emphasis box="[1263,1436,839,863]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">S. ponticeriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Duvernoy" box="[380,573,874,899]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" refString="Duvernoy, L. G. (1846) Atlas (Les reptiles). Le Regne animal distribue d'apres son organisation, pour servir de base a l'histoire naturelle des animaux et d'introduction a l'anatomie comparee, plate 16." type="book chapter" year="1846">
Duvernoy (
<number box="[506,565,874,899]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" value="1846.0">1846</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but which corresponds to 
<taxonomicName box="[869,1032,874,899]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Sitana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="deccanensis">
<emphasis box="[869,1032,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">S. deccanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,1115]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,886,910,935]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
Variation in the second 
<typeStatus box="[507,599,910,935]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">syntype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[620,709,910,935]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">BMNH</collectionCode>
1946.8.27.40).
</emphasis>
<number box="[900,928,910,935]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" value="66.0">66</number>
scale rows around midbody; ventrals, 
<number box="[1400,1431,911,935]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" value="83.0">83</number>
; subdigital lamellae on the toe IV, 
<number box="[527,558,947,971]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" value="23.0">23</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,1115]" box="[199,1360,982,1007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,519,982,1007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Suggested common names.</emphasis>
English name: Deccan Fan-throat Lizard; French name: Sitane du Deccan.
</paragraph>
